'14:21': [
{sup:"1a", word:"four", vrefs:"Rev. 6:8", lines:["The four means, given here and in {Ezk5:17|5:17}, by which God exercised His judgment on His Old Testament people typify the means used by God to judge His degraded New Testament elect, the church ({1Pe4:17|1&nbsp;Pet. 4:17}): dissension (sword), a lack of spiritual food (famine), spiritual diseases (pestilence), and evil persons (wild beasts&mdash;cf. {Act20:29|Acts 20:29}). The results of God&rsquo;s judgment on Israel, His degraded elect, were (1) the loss of the good land ({Ezk14:15|v. 15}; {Ezk7:21|7:21}; {2Ch36:9|2&nbsp;Chron. 36:9}-{2Ch36:10|10}, {2Ch36:17|17}, {2Ch36:20|20}; {Jer52:15|Jer. 52:15}), typifying the loss of the enjoyment of Christ ({Gal5:2|Gal. 5:2}-{Gal5:4|4}); (2) the departing of the glory of the Lord ({Ezk9:3|9:3}; {Ezk11:22|11:22}-{Ezk11:23|23}), signifying the departing of God&rsquo;s manifestation from the church ({Rev2:5|Rev. 2:5}; cf. {1Ti3:15|1&nbsp;Tim. 3:15}-{1Ti3:16|16}; {1Co14:25|1&nbsp;Cor. 14:25}); and (3) the destruction of the temple and the burning of the city ({Ezk33:21|33:21}; {2Ch36:19|2&nbsp;Chron. 36:19}; {Jer52:12|Jer. 52:12}-{Jer52:14|14}), signifying the loss of God&rsquo;s dwelling place and God&rsquo;s kingdom from the church (cf. {Eph2:20|Eph. 2:20}-{Eph2:22|22}; {Rom14:17|Rom. 14:17})."]},
],
